cookie package¶

Submodules¶

cookie.GraphDR module¶

Implements GraphDR, a graph-regularized dimensionality reduction method for single-cell or high-dimensional data.

cookie.GraphDR.graphdr(pca_data, lambda_=1, no_rotation=True, n_neighbor=10, top_d_eigenvector=10)[source]¶

Main Function of GraphDR mehtod

Parameters:

  • pca_data (numpy.ndarray) -- PCA results of the original data (n, d)

  • lambda (float) -- Parameters to control the regularization on Laplacian matrix

  • no_rotation (bool) -- Control if the final results need to be rotated based on the eigenvector

  • n_neighbor (int) -- Number of neighbor when constructing neighbor graph

  • top_d_eigenvector (int) -- number of eigenvectors to choose when performing rotation

Returns:

Z -- The final graph-regularized dimension reduction results;(n, top_d_eigenvector) if no_rotation False; (n, d) else

Return type:

numpy.ndarray

cookie.GraphDR.preprocess_data(data)[source]¶

Preprocess and normalize the single cell data

Parameters:

data (numpy.ndarray) -- The original single cell or sequencing data (n, d)

Returns:

preprocessed_data -- Data after normalization for each cell (n, d)

Return type:

numpy.ndarray

Compute entropy(H) and probability(P) from nxn distance matrix.

Parameters:

  • beta (float) -- precision measure

Returns:

  • H (float) -- entropy

  • P (numpy.ndarray) -- probability matrix (n,n)

cookie.adjustbeta.adjustbeta(X, tol, perplexity)[source]¶

Precision(beta) adjustment based on perplexity

Parameters:

  • X (numpy.ndarray) -- data input array with dimension (n,d)

  • tol (float) -- tolerance for the stopping criteria of beta adjustment

  • perplexity (float) -- perplexity can be interpreted as a smooth measure of the effective number of neighbors

Returns:

  • P (numpy.ndarray) -- probability matrix (n,n)

  • beta (numpy.ndarray) -- precision array (n,1)
